#Is python an object oriented programming language ?
In python everything is an object and can be handled as such.
For example, functions are first-class objects.
Functions, classes, string and types are objects.
They all can be passes as function arguments.

#Is python like Java ?
Unlike Java, Python does not impose object-oriented programming as the main paradigm.
It viable to have a project without object-oriented design.

#How to do some unit tests ?
#https://docs.python.org/fr/3/library/unittest.html
Create a package ./tests
Run python -m unittest tests/test_calculator.py